<br>
Lady C <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/usirlageholyblaze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Lage Holyblaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/24/01 1:32:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The time approcahes...</span><hr size=1> Dallllllllinnnnnn.  Hehe scouts are the Albion equivalent of the Hibernian Ranger or the Midgard Hunter.  Massive archery damage, sneak/hide/climb, etc.  The only differences from the EQ ranger are: *much* better archery damage (lots of types of archery too -- volley shot, aimed shot, long shot, etc.) but less on the AC (studded leather as max armor) and less and the damage dealing (cannot dual wield, though dual wield may not be as much king in DAoC is it was in EQ).  Scouts do use shield and get some nice disciplines to go with them.<br>
<br>
On the first day, I'll probably start a Paladin, a Mercenary, a Scout and perhaps an Infiltrator and a friar.  I'll play a little of each and see who I like the most.<br>
<br>
As for GL, it's a bit too soon to make decisions due to the fact that DAoC guilds are not limited to monarchy command structures.  There is not just GL, officers, members; it can be almost anything though exactly what the entails is under NDA so we won't know for another month or so.  I do know that actual ranks can be assigned, as can the guild be lead (share power) with multiple people (multiple GL's pretty much).<br>
<br>
You ascertation that a GL with be a figurehead in DAoC is correct  With just people that we already know being the core of the guild and if we implement very strict recruitement policies, then the maintenance of the guild will be quite small (like PR was originally).<br>
<br>
Personally, I forsee having time to manage a small guild of friends (40 - 60 or so) as I expect to be able to play several nights a week, and most of the weekend nights around that time.  However, I won't have time to lead it if it becomes a uberguild.  The amount of time neccesary to run those correctly is phenomenal.<br>
<br>
When beta 5 begins, I imagine we will have the server names at that time.  If the NDA is lifted before that time and the guild structure is released, I'd like to meet in a chat room of sorts and begin to discuss the details with those that plan to move to DAoC and would like to form a guild together.  Also, at that time with the appropriate information, we can then decide of form of govrnment as well as GL if the monarchy route is chosen or the &quot;heads&quot; if a shared GL route is chosen.  Then we just pick a server, finalize the realm and jump into some action =).  <br>
